oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Grazing where waterway will be
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: "Before" picture of a portion of seven tenths acre sod waterway to be shaped and seeded on Class four Guthrie soil. Entire field will be reestablished to fescue and white clover when waterways are contructed. Located twelve miles southwest of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
